cs.DB, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE 

This paper is about benchmarking deductive databases and rule engines, which are typically studied in the fields of databases (cs.DB), programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on the performance of bottom-up evaluation, which is a common technique used in deductive databases and rule engines. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB and cs.PL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LO, and cs.SE.
